'''Mint Condition''' is an expression used in the description of pre-owned goods. "Mint" means "used, but still as new". Originally, the phrase comes from the way collectors describe the condition of coins. As the name given to a coin factory is a 'mint', then mint condition is the condition a coin is in as it leaves the mint. But why is a coin factory called a mint?

